---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Toolkit tools are designed to process text and files locally in your browser whenever possible. Learn what is and is not collected."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <main class="page-shell section prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Toolkit is designed around a simple promise: your tool input should stay in your browser whenever the tool can run locally. Current text tools transform and count text on your device and do not upload what you type.
    </p>
    <h2>Tool input</h2>
    <p>
      We do not receive, store, or process the text you enter into the Fancy Text Generator. The transformation is handled by JavaScript running in your browser.
    </p>
    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      The site may use privacy-friendly analytics to understand page visits and improve the product. Analytics must not record the text you type into tools.
    </p>
    <h2>Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      Advertising is disabled at launch. If ads are enabled later, ad code will be isolated from tool state and must not be used to collect your tool input.
    </p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      This policy will be updated as new tools are added. File-processing tools will include clear notes about local browser processing before launch.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
